 {"id":"flywheel_gateway-bpg","title":"FEAT: UBS Scanner Integration","description":"## Background

UBS (Ultimate Bug Scanner) provides automated code analysis capabilities for detecting issues, vulnerabilities, and improvement opportunities across codebases. This integration enables Flywheel Gateway to leverage UBS for proactive code quality management with the unique ability to automatically create beads from findings.

## Reasoning

Manual code review catches issues but:
- Is time-consuming and inconsistent
- Misses patterns that automated tools detect
- Creates friction in the development workflow
- Findings often get lost or forgotten

UBS provides automated scanning with findings that can be directly converted to actionable beads, ensuring issues are tracked, prioritized, and resolved through the standard Flywheel workflow.

## Technical Considerations

### Client Architecture
- Follow flywheel-clients pattern
- Support async scanning with progress callbacks
- Handle large scan results efficiently
- Integrate with BV for bead creation

### API Design
```typescript
interface UBSClient {
  // Scan Operations
  startScan(config: ScanConfig): Promise<ScanJob>;
  getScanStatus(jobId: string): Promise<ScanStatus>;
  cancelScan(jobId: string): Promise<void>;
  getScanResults(jobId: string): Promise<ScanResults>;

  // Findings
  getFindings(filters?: FindingFilters): Promise<Finding[]>;
  getFindingById(id: string): Promise<Finding>;
  getFindingsBySeverity(): Promise<GroupedFindings>;
  dismissFinding(id: string, reason: DismissReason): Promise<void>;
  bulkDismiss(ids: string[], reason: DismissReason): Promise<void>;

  // Auto-Bead
  createBeadFromFinding(findingId: string, options?: BeadOptions): Promise<Bead>;
  bulkCreateBeads(findingIds: string[], options?: BeadOptions): Promise<Bead[]>;

  // History
  getScanHistory(filters?: HistoryFilters): Promise<ScanSummary[]>;
  compareScanResults(scanId1: string, scanId2: string): Promise<ScanComparison>;
  getTrends(period: TrendPeriod): Promise<TrendData>;
}

interface ScanConfig {
  projectPath: string;
  scanTypes?: ('security' | 'quality' | 'performance' | 'style')[];
  excludePaths?: string[];
  severity?: SeverityLevel[];
  rulesets?: string[];
  incremental?: boolean;
}

interface Finding {
  id: string;
  type: string;
  severity: 'critical' | 'high' | 'medium' | 'low' | 'info';
  title: string;
  description: string;
  file: string;
  line?: number;
  column?: number;
  codeSnippet?: string;
  suggestedFix?: string;
  rule: string;
  tags: string[];
  status: 'open' | 'dismissed' | 'fixed' | 'converted';
  createdAt: Date;
  convertedBeadId?: string;
}

interface ScanResults {
  jobId: string;
  status: 'completed' | 'failed' | 'partial';
  findings: Finding[];
  summary: {
    total: number;
    bySeverity: Record<SeverityLevel, number>;
    byType: Record<string, number>;
  };
  duration: number;
  coverage: number;
}
```

